Description:
Country Living!
This 11 acre property has been well developed to suit the horse enthusiast however it will suit a variety of interests.
The home offers 3 good sized bedrooms (outdoor 6 person spa to main), lounge room, separate kitchen/dining area, air conditioning & heating.Off the main bedroom is walk through robe which could easily undergo renovation to ensuite. Carport under roof line combing with rear outdoor area.
Dual access to the front of the property, being extremely well treed & fenced there are 8 paddocks with walk in boxes, 5 day paddocks with walk in boxes plus 7 indoor brick stables, tack room & washing facilities.
Magnificently treed & excellent fencing layout.
11 acres situated minutes from Cobram, this property represents value for money.

Description:
Premium Stone Fruit Orchard
COBRAM STONE FRUIT ORCHARD
A progressive enterprise with state of the art irrigation equipment geared to supply the fresh fruit market.
The property comprises approximately 50,000 mostly young tree plantings of new and current market trend varieties.
Full production potential on the orchard is expected 2013 2014 growing season.
The property has excellent water security with a total available water entitlement of 715 megalitres from ground and gravity and storage supplies.
A 20 megalitre on farm storage dam gives the property enormous flexibility for frost prevention, early season irrigation and at call water application when required.
Land description
Soil types are mostly free draining red loam and red sandy loam soils and a smaller portion of grey clay loam that is hilled and trellised.
Improvements are of excellent quality and consisting of:
Packing shed 18.5m x 33.8m, office and staff amenities block.
Cool Store Complex, 24.5m x 8.9divided (490 bin capacity) into 3 rooms with 7.5kw compressor units to each compartment.
Lockup Machinery/Bin Shed 24.9m x 18.2m and 7m x 7m incorporated Workshop.
7.3m x 15m open front Machinery Shed.
12.8m x 9.2m open front Machinery Shed.
13.4m x 4m open front Machinery Shed.
4m x 4m Chemical Shed, adjacent cement standing area and filling station.
Irrigation
Water:
the property has an irrigation delivery share of 2.16 megalitres /day and 284 Megalitre Ground water (Bore) Licence.
Optional Water Share:
High Reliability Water Share of 216.4 megalitres & a Low Reliability water Share 214.6 megalitres are available to the successful purchaser at an agreed value.
